laboratory_examinations.findings: Bilateral linear atelectasis otherwise no abnormality demonstrated. Right lobe of the liver air hyperdensity, 2 cm in diameter, low in density most likely representing cysts. Substantial thickening and fat stranding surrounding the appendix which approaches at least 12 mm in diameter fluid-filled with potential small amount of fluid surrounding it. No free air demonstrated. A partially calcified diverticulum, 14 x 17.5 mm, adjacent but separated from the bladder.
